The paper deals with energy minimization in multiuser wireless systems using OFDM, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus is on optimizing the transmission and reception of data in a wireless network, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of different transmission strategies and multiple access schemes, which could fall under cs.SY and cs.MM. Finally, the paper proposes a flexible range of energy consumption tradeoffs, which could be related to optimization and machine learning, hence cs.LG is also a possible category.
